5
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:49,640
I would answer, “Not at all.”

6
00:02:51,920 --> 00:02:56,960
However, I often wonder,
instead of telling my parents directly,

7
00:02:57,920 --> 00:03:01,320
If there was a better way to let them know

8
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:04,000
I am “different” from other kids

9
00:03:08,440 --> 00:03:10,880
If I had not told them,

10
00:03:10,920 --> 00:03:13,560
would things have gone on differently?

11
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:15,000
How was it?

12
00:03:16,360 --> 00:03:17,800
Did you tell them?

13
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:20,800
Would the relationships between me,
father, mother and Roger,

14
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:22,000
have been different?

15
00:03:22,080 --> 00:03:23,720
How did they react?

16
00:03:34,960 --> 00:03:38,640
Someone once told me,
if you close your eyes

17
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:42,680
Imagine when you are in your 70s or 80s

18
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:46,600
Sitting on a wheel chair,
needing help to go to the toilet

19
00:03:47,440 --> 00:03:50,480
and you can imagine
the one pushing your wheel chair

20
00:03:51,040 --> 00:03:52,840
is the one next to you

21
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:56,240
He’s the one worth
spending your whole life with

22
00:03:58,480 --> 00:04:02,680
There was no love at first sight,
nor was there fairytale-love between me and Roger

23
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:06,360
There were only stories of daily life,
one after another.

24
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:10,280
What we remember

25
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:13,320
is perhaps like the photos stored on your phone

26
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:17,120
I remember, that year at the LGBT parade

27
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:19,040
was the first time
we held hands out in the open

28
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:20,080
and kissed in public.

29
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:22,800
It was then that I knew

30
00:04:22,880 --> 00:04:29,400
How to ignore other people’s peculiar looks
and be honest with myself

31
