I major in physics,
I work part-time as a cook

41
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:22,000
You can excel in every field.
I didn’t even graduate from primary school

42
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:26,960
and I living in public housing,

43
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:37,080
Uncle, have some chicken, here
- Oh, that’s ok, I can help myself

44
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:38,200
Auntie, have some too

45
00:05:41,440 --> 00:05:42,440
Let me give you an red envolope

46
00:05:44,760 --> 00:05:46,080
Thank you Auntie
- May all your wishes come true!

47
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:47,840
Thank you Auntie.

48
00:06:00,320 --> 00:06:02,800
Why am I with this person?

49
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:07,160
For a while,
I asked myself this question everyday

50
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:12,840
To what extent do we have to understand
a person in order to be with him?

51
00:06:12,840 --> 00:06:17,160
How much of that person do
we possess when we say we are in a relationship?

52
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:23,440
At the beginning, I felt anxious

53
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:26,440
This feeling came from
occupying the same space

54
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:28,760
yet not knowing what he was thinking about

55
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:29,720
I am going to the toilet

56
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:38,320
That made me uneasy

57
00:06:39,200 --> 00:06:44,480
I asked myself every day,
what kept us together?

58
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:49,680
Some people call this sense of unease
an insight into the future,

59
00:06:50,920 --> 00:06:53,840
But even though everyone has
this kind of insight

60
00:06:55,360 --> 00:06:58,480
I chose to deal with it only
when I am forced to do so

61
00:07:12,360 --> 00:07:13,960
You wanna go for dinner?

62
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:22,120
Ricky！Ricky！

63
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:24,960
Hey!

64
00:07:25,280 --> 00:07:26,280
Hey!

65
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:29,800
Listen!

66
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:32,720
Listen!

67
00:08:50,160 --> 00:08:52,760
Why am I still with you?

68
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:57,520
It was Sept, 2014

69
00:08:58,880 --> 00:09:02,760
Ever since Sept, 2014,
whenever I heard the sound of fireworks,

70
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:04,240
I felt suffocated

71
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:07,160
Unknowingly,
whenever I heard the sound of fireworks,

72
00:09:07,160 --> 00:09:08,800
My eyes would fill with tears

73
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:10,720
I recalled the moment
when the police fired tear gas

74
00:09:11,080 --> 00:09:15,280
Today, the Hong Kong government re-opened
the Civic Square to the public.

75
00:09:15,280 --> 00:09:18,360
Last month, the Legislative Council passed
the Marriage Ordinance amendment

76
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:21,960
Same-sex marriage became legal in Hong Kong

77
00:09:23,120 --> 00:09:28,240
That same week, the 8400th tear gas
was fired just outside the Legislative Council

78
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:33,400
The first same-sex marriage ceremony in Hong Kong was held

79
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:36,040
at a time of social and political conflict and anti-government sentiment

80
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:38,200
Why am I still with you?

81
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:42,040
After holding hands for the first time in public during the LGBT parade

82
00:09:42,760 --> 00:09:45,480
I held Roger’s hand for the second time during the Umbrella Movement

83
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:47,960
When the police fired tear gas and charged towards us

84
00:09:48,480 --> 00:09:52,760
We ran hand in hand from Harcourt Road to the Academy for Performing Arts

85
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:56,920
and onwards to the Chinese Methodist Church in Wan Chai

86
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:30,680
Today, you come in the front of God

87
00:10:30,680 --> 00:10:34,720
Your families, your friends

88
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:36,960
to bear witness to your love for one another

89
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:42,040
Do you promise, in the presence of God and everyone present

90
00:10:42,040 --> 00:10:47,040
to take each other for your lawful wedded husband

91
00:10:47,040 --> 00:10:48,040
Roger Fung

92
00:10:49,960 --> 00:10:50,960
I do

93
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:52,360
Ricky Tsang

94
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:55,600
I do

95
00:10:56,040 --> 00:10:57,040
Mandy Man

96
00:10:57,680 --> 00:10:58,680
I do

97
00:10:59,480 --> 00:11:00,480
Cecilia Ho

98
00:11:01,280 --> 00:11:02,240
I do

99
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:20,120
Now I pronounce you lawfully wedded husbands and wives

100
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:29,280
I have never thought it could happen,
that we can get married

101
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:31,960
Because… -You can say it

102
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:34,720
She was hospitalised

103
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:39,680
